Preheat your oven to 200°C. Quarter the @salad potatoes{350%g}. Peel the @carrot{1%whole} and remove both ends, then quarter lengthways and chop the lengths into three chunks. Put the potatoes and carrot on a #baking tray{} and drizzle over some @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and sprinkle over the half the @dried Italian herbs{1/2%tsp}. Toss to coat, then roast on the middle shelf of your oven until golden and cooked through, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Put the @British chicken thighs{4} on another baking tray. Sprinkle on the remaining Italian herbs and season with salt and pepper. Rub the seasoning into the chicken. TIP: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat! Pop on the top shelf of your oven and roast until the skin is crispy, ~{30-35%minutes}. TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, remove the root and dark green top from the @leek{1/2}(sliced into 1cm thick rounds), then slice into 1cm thick rounds. Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1/2}(cut into 3 pieces per quarter lengthways), quarter lengthways and chop each strip into three pieces. Add the leek and courgette to the potatoes and carrot after ~{15%minutes} of cooking time, mixing them in evenly. Roast until soft and golden, ~{20%minutes}.

Cut the @premium tomato mix{112.5%g} in half through the equator. Pop into a #mixing bowl{}. Chop each @medium tomato{1} into eight pieces. Add these to the bowl and season with a pinch of salt. Stir in a glug of @olive oil{1%tbsp} (see ingredients for amount). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{7.5%g}(chopped finely, stalks and all) and stir a quarter into the tomato salad. TIP: The salt will help the tomatoes release their juice and make a delicious dressing.

Pick the @mint{1/2%bunch}(picked from stalks, roughly chopped) leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Mix the mint and remaining parsley together in another mixing bowl with the @honey{7.5%ml}, @wholegrain mustard{1/2%tbsp} (add less if you don't love mustard!), @red wine vinegar{1/2%tbsp} and @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} (see ingredients for amount). Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Keep to one side.

Share the roasted veggies and tomato salad between your plates and place the chicken thighs alongside. Spoon the minty salsa on top. Enjoy!